NAME

internsctl - A tool for managing interns

SYNOPSIS

internsctl [COMMAND]

DESCRIPTION

The internsctl tool is a command-line tool for managing interns. It can be used to create and manage intern accounts, list interns, and get information about interns.

COMMANDS

cpu: Get CPU information.

memory: Get memory information.

user: Manage intern accounts.

create: Create a new intern account.

list: List all intern accounts.

list --sudo-only: List all intern accounts with sudo permissions.

file: Get information about files.

getinfo: Get information about a file.

getinfo --size: Get the size of a file.

getinfo --permissions: Get the permissions of a file.

getinfo --owner: Get the owner of a file.

getinfo --last-modified: Get the last modified date of a file.

version: Display the version of the internsctl script.


EXAMPLES

To get CPU information, type:
internsctl cpu

To get memory information, type:
internsctl memory

To create a new intern account, type:
internsctl user create <username>

To list all intern accounts, type:
internsctl user list

To list all intern accounts with sudo permissions, type:
internsctl user list --sudo-only

To get information about the file /etc/passwd, type:
internsctl file getinfo /etc/passwd

To get the size of the file /etc/passwd, type:
internsctl file getinfo --size /etc/passwd

To get the permissions of the file /etc/passwd, type:
internsctl file getinfo --permissions /etc/passwd

To get the owner of the file /etc/passwd, type:
internsctl file getinfo --owner /etc/passwd

To get the last modified date of the file /etc/passwd, type:
internsctl file getinfo --last-modified /etc/passwd

To display the version of the internsctl script, type:
internsctl --version

